go_data.justification: SEPT12 orchestrates the formation of mammalian sperm annulus by organizing core octameric complexes with other SEPT proteins.
SEPT12 mutations cause male infertility with defective sperm annulus.
SEPT12 interacts with other septin proteins found in the SEPT2, SEPT6, and SEPT7 protein subgroups to form a filamentous structure at the sperm annulus.
SEPT12 is known to interact with other septin proteins to form a filamentous structure at the sperm annulus.
